<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I'll start off by saying that I was never a big charm fan to begin with.  But I've recently been reading up on the posts here concerning it and have decided to give it another go.  Being a newly appointed 45th lvl chanter, I figure it's about time I be able to do some damage on my own in the Dreadlands.  (Up till now I havent tried soloing this zone)  Well, seeing all the praise charm soloing is getting, and the fact that I also don't think my pet could handle these mobs without severe mana loss on my part.  I deside to go the charm route.  Well, the concept and tactics seem simple enough.. except i seem to have a problem keeping my mob charmed for over 30 seconds.  I've tried for over an hour and not once did a charm last for over 30 secs. Most broke within about 15 or so.  I didn't think my 153 CHA was THAT bad.  Did I just have a bad night? or is this charm thing not all its cracked up to be.  Recastng Cajoling whispers every 15 secs or so gets mana costly.  I'd rather stick with the pet..  at least then i only have to deal with one mob wanting to beat the hell outta me instead of two.  Any thoughts?  <P>Shokran<BR>45th Enchanter
</FONT>
