<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Shokran you didn't go into depth about your tactics but things that you might consider would be the level of the MOBs you're trying to charm.  At 45 you're sort of on the low to middle end for DL and if you're trying to charm mid or high level blues you can't expect charm to stick for too long.  Also, are you tashing before charming?  That'll probably help increase the length of the charm in the long run as well.  Also, certain types of MOBs have higher resists than others, if I remember correctly the chickens in DL have pretty high resists compared to some of the other MOBS.  Hope some of that helps, I wouldn't give up too quickly.<P>--------------------<P>Malekith V'rdeen<BR>56 Enchanter <BR>53 Druid<BR>Tarrew Marr-Dragonkin
</FONT>
