<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Charming is not the be all and end all, uber tactic to end all uber tactics.  It *IS* a very useful tool though, and it's good to be able to whip it out of the toolbox when you need it.<P>I had a hell of a time when I first started charming.  Luckily, I had a great group of friends who endured my charming mishaps long enough to allow me to get confident with it.  You WILL have short charms and you WILL have long charms.  Last night in the hole on a 5 pull, I had an elemental crusader charmed through the entire fight... finally had to pillage the charm at the end so we could take him down, and amazingly enough he dropped one of my three pieces of loam I got last night. =)  I also had my fair share of 15 sec charms too.<P>I don't charm all the time, but I do charm when I feel it's appropriate.  I recommend that you practice with a group of people (a few friends who won't mind enduring some trials at the start) instead of soloing, until you get comfortable with it, and then keep it handy for when you need it.  And remember, sometimes keeping 'em stacked up with mez is plenty fine, too.<P>-- Faenyar<P>--------------------<P>Druzzil Ro server
</FONT>
