<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The level of the mob you are trying to charm is the most important thing.  I've never hunted in the DL so I don't know what level ranges the mobs are, but you want to try and get a low blue or even a mob that just turned green if possible.  You will get longer duration charms.  And if you slow the mob you're fighting your pet shouldn't get killed.  Or even better yet don't slow the mob you're fighting and let your charmed pet get killed.  Then you can finish nuking the other mob to death and you will get full xp instead of just half.<P>Wandatin Dai'Noga
