Bloodgills, wow. I can tell ya after spending a ton of time in Kedge that underwater is not the place to learn charm tactics.  Despite other advantages of the particular mobs (i.e. if they have low MR, they may make nice pets), the disadvantage of the environment is very high.<BR>   Underwater, every hit has increased knockback, which greatly decreases your ability to channel though the hit and get a spell off.  If you do as the poster suggested and run, you can get away, however, it takes time to camp and return that you could otherwise spend fighting.<BR>   So, though its possible, it would be more tricky and require greater skill to learn to charm solo underwater, and I would spend a few levels practicing to do it.<P>   Someone suggested SOW, and combining this with druid ensnare (the longer lasting variety) can really add a lot of power to your charming.  Also, fear the target mob, so your pet doesn't get damaged and you'll be able to keep the same pet for up to 10 to 15 fights before you run out of mana if you are lucky.<P>   This is only half the learning curve though. Outdoor fighting is one thing, but indoor charm fighting is totally different.  It involves mainly realizing that there is no where to run and different tactics.  Slow the targt, use flux/shift and L4Mez to regain pet control, root and/or L4Mez on target to keep him parked while you regain control, throw in pet haste and weapons when you get really good, and don't attempt indoor charm fighting tactics without a cleric for buffs and heals.  Make sure that the healer and you stick together for the whole learning curve. Basicly, the healer should be casting fast full heals (sup heal, remedy) when pet breaks but before he even can see that you are taking damage (with hasted, duelwielding pet).  If the healer has as long as a 20 second response time, you will die if you have a string of bad channelings or stuns.<P>Both sets of tacts are independent, require different spell sets, different tacts and are better suited for different environments.<P>The Ph.D. level of charm fighting is indoor giant charming while fighting unmezable giants in Kael  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Elly Of Innoruuk<BR>Enchantress (52)
