<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I don't know how in the hell I forgot to mention this.<P>45th level.<BR>Dreadlands.<P>Mez-Kite.<P>Load your level 4 mez up, Discordant and Anarchy (for finishing nukes) and get SoW.<P>Tash a spider, run till recast clears, then spin and mez.  If you spin your movement stops instantly, and you now have a spider ready to kill.  During the next 24 seconds, run off a bit, and nuke it.  (Root if you like, when it holds--about half the time--it's nice, but I had JBoots and didn't care.)  Right as the casting box vanishes start running.  The nuke will hit and you run till the recast clears, then remez.<P>You can do this all day at no risk, spiders are everywhere (people don't like to pull them a lot if they can help it) and it only takes about 3 nukes to have them dead or fleeing that last Anarchy to dump them.  I used typically 40% of my mana each pull, and it was fast, clean, risk-free (virtually) and gave me the chance to solo a little when I wasn't in the mood (or had time) to group.<P>Only change from when I did that is that Root no longer kills SoW, so avoid drachnid recluses, who will SoW themselves, and spiders walking very fast because a recluse buffed them.  If you open with a dispel that can be removed, but there's plenty of spiders to go around.<P>I didn't charm solo in DL heavily until 47th.  (Or charm a lot at all.)<P>My <B>second</B> enchanter (total non-twink) is for charm soloing, and I've done so since 12th.  I play that character because I enjoy charm soloing so much.  Charm soloing is dangerous and a rush of adrenaline.  While that necro has an easier time staring at a running mob doomed from the start, I'm keeping a tenuous hold on deaths... mine and my enemies.<P>--------------------<P>Eugee<P><A HREF="http://www.cyberjunkie.com/eugee" TARGET=_blank>Xornn's Guide to Enchanting</A><P><I>"You know, we scientists learned long ago that human interaction was impossible to predict; so we left that up to the philosophers... and poets."</I>
