I dunno, I learned to charm underwater at the Bloodgills. Since then I've charmed in Guk, Karnors (fun to charm the two at the zone in so you can walk right past), and a few other places. I used rune3, and sometimes 4 so that I could still cast when things go wrong. You do get pushed slightly back, but you can still cast when you are rune'd. That few seconds of room allowed me to root, back off and start it over again.<BR>Enthrall works best as does regular ole root. I was petrified of using charm before, but now I'm pretty confident about it. Kinda fun to freak out groups once in a while and you tell them "k, charming"<P>--------------------<P>"One target pls!"<BR>Caenem  <BR>Caveo Ervum<BR>RZ
