Mini stay puff marshmellow FG's are fun too  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0"> got one shrunk twice, he's about the same size as me in gnome illusion.<BR>Well, in all honestly, for charm soloing, pump your cha.  That is, I repeat, MY OPINION.  There have been tests, and all that questioning it, but hey...It is really really easy to get your cha to around 200, try it with high cha and compare your results.  If you are concerned about the mana loss...med up with 200 int, buff yourself, drop int for cha gear =).<P>outdoors with no healer, distance is the only thing that matters.  Don't be a hero and try to channel off anything outdoors, there isn't any point to that.  Even with jboots you can outrun anything in dl (well...MOST, just steer clear of spiders).  A GRRREAT place to learn/practice charm soloing is the little yeti cave by the Tunnel in DL.  They have REALLY low MR, and there's enough space where you can run to recharm.  There's lots of ways to get control, you can root, lvl 4 mez, chainstun.  Depends on what your doing really.  It is a pain to find profitable charm solo spots, but you can kill nearly anything solo using charm.  Just some take more time.  Rumors about a good place to solo in CS..I haven't gone to CS since that little goof by VI putting the wuoshi breath on the drakes there...<BR>hmmm.......<P><BR>Balls<P>--------------------<P>Cannial<BR>Enchanter of Quellious<BR>Member of Lotus Cult
